natural solution: Multiplying the numerator and denominator by the conjugate of the denominator, we have \begin{align} \dfrac{3+4i}{1+2i} \cdot \frac{1-2i}{1-2i} &= \frac{3(1) + 3(-2i) + 4i(1) + 4i(-2i)}{1(1) + 1(-2i) + 2i(1) -2i(2i)} \\
